Date: Wed 4 Sep 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2019 [edited] https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31644


African swine fever, Hong Kong (SAR - PRC)
------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 4 Sep 2019 from Dr. Thomas Sit, chief veterinary officer/assistant director (Inspection & Quarantine), Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government, Hong Kong, Hong Kong (SAR - PRC)

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Sep 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 3 Sep 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2 Jun 2019
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Sheung Shui Slaughterhouse, New Territories, Hong Kong
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2019
Outbreak status: Resolved 3 Sep 2019
Epidemiological unit: Slaughterhouse
Total affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / - / 3 / 3 / - / -
Affected population: Samples of kidney, spleen, and lymph node from 3 imported pigs tested positive for African swine fever virus.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Legal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: An African swine fever surveillance system is in place for local pig farms, slaughterhouses, and wild boars in Hong Kong. The virus was detected in tissue samples collected as part of the surveillance system from 3 imported pigs that died in the slaughterhouse. A daily clearance arrangement has been implemented in the slaughterhouses. Lairages in different areas of the slaughterhouse are cleared out with thorough cleansing and disinfection every day. Cleaning and disinfection of vehicles transporting pigs have also been enhanced.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; screening; traceability; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; stamping out; disinfection; ante- and post-mortem inspections; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Tai Lung Veterinary Laboratory, Agriculture Fisheries and Conservation Department (national laboratory) / Swine / Polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 3 Sep 2019 / Positive
Tai Lung Veterinary Laboratory, Agriculture Fisheries and Conservation Department (national laboratory) / Swine / Real-time PCR / 3 Sep 2019 / Positive
The Pirbright Institute (OIE reference laboratory) / Swine / Real-time PCR / - / Pending

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 3rd case of African swine fever reported by Hong Kong since the disease was 1st reported in May 2019 when 2 outbreaks were notified. In both the previous outbreaks and in the current outbreak, the virus was detected in tissue samples collected from pigs in the slaughterhouse. The events reported in May have been resolved. See event summaries and maps at https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30449 and https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?reportid=30685. - Mod.CRD

